## Minimal Configuration

Financial Charts come pre-configured with built-in features - just add your data!

{% if isFramework("javascript") %}

```js
const options = {
    data: getData(),
};

AgCharts.createFinancialChart(options);
```

{% /if %}

{% if isFramework("react") %}

```jsx
const [options, setOptions] = useState({
    data: getData(),
});

return (
    <AgFinancialCharts options={options} />
);
```

{% /if %}

{% if isFramework("angular") %}

```js
@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  standalone: true,
  imports: [AgFinancialCharts],
  template: `<ag-financial-charts [options]="options"></ag-financial-charts>`,
})
export class AppComponent {
  public options: AgFinancialChartOptions;
  constructor() {
    this.options = {
      data: getData(),
    };
  }
}
```

{% /if %}

{% if isFramework("vue") %}

```js
template: `<ag-financial-charts:options="options"/>`,
components: {
    'ag-financial-charts': AgFinancialCharts,
},
data() {
    return {
        options: {
            data: getData(),
        },
    };
}
```

{% /if %}

{% note %}
This snippet assumes the supplied data includes 'date', 'open', 'high', 'low', 'close' and 'volume' (optional) keys.
{% /note %}

For more details see [Financial Charts Configuration](./financial-charts-configuration/).

## Drawings and Annotations

Add and manage [Trend Lines](./financial-charts-toolbar#lines) and [Text Annotations](./financial-charts-toolbar#annotations) from the intuitive toolbar for enhanced data analysis.

